ğŸ“ Right-Angled Triangle Star Pattern in Java
This Java program prints a right-angled triangle pattern made of asterisks (*). 
The triangle is aligned to the left side, with its right angle at the bottom-left corner. 
It is a perfect beginner exercise for understanding nested loops and incremental pattern printing in Java.


import java.util.*;
public class Righttriangle {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		// TODO Auto-generated method stub
		Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
		int n = sc.nextInt();
		for(int i=1;i<=n;i++) {
			for(int j=1;j<=i;j++) {
				System.out.print("* ");
			}
			System.out.println();
		}
	}

}

 Sample Input/Output:
Input:
5
Output:
* 
* * 
* * * 
* * * * 
* * * * * 

Scanner class for reading user input

for loops for repetition

Nested loops for row-column structure

Basic logic for increasing pattern printing
